Job Highlights 

Solid exp in e-Commerce & Social Media 2-3 years
Work independently for operating an online shop
Knowledge use of web page, photoshop & AI design marketing materials

Job Description

A newly set up on-line shop is looking for a competent, reliable and agile candidate to fill up a position of E-Commence Officer to manage and boost the sales of our  e-Commerce platforms including but not limited to our online shops, to design and prepare marketing materials for both the online shops and showroom.

Duties and Responsibilities

Fully responsible to operate this online shop and showroom independently;
Responsibilities including but not limited to online sales, marketing and daily Operation of this online shop;
Perform & manage operation of this online shop and on different selling channels and  E-Commerce portals; 
Manage daily operations of online shop including generate & update website content (product listing, data entry, promotions, etc);
Effective use of SEO, social media and KOLs to promote our products, e.g. through Facebook, Instagram, Google AD, WeChat group and 小紅書 etc;
Knowledge of video shooting, editing and daily video production;
Analyze and monitor online shop statistics and daily sales data to optimize channel traffic performance and sales; 
Modify weekly product arrangements and make suggestions to change online shop layouts; 
Create & implement tactical offers to support specific products and target specific market;
Other ad-hoc assignments.

Requirements

Degree in Journalism & Communication or related discipline;
2+ year relevant experience in E-commerce platform related, (fresh graduated will be considered);
Possess well-developed design skills and marketing knowledge – capable to use photoshops, AI for design and preparing marketing materials;
Good knowledge of SEO, SEM, Goggle analytics and adwords;
Experience with logistic arrangement and warehouse management is advantage;
Proficient in MS Office (MS Word, Excel, Powerpoint, Outlook);
Capable to work independently;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (include Mandarin).

Availability commencement :

Around February, 2022 (after CNY holiday)

Working days :

5 days per week

Tue–Sat (09:30~18:30); Sun & Mon Rest day

Responsibilities:


Coordinate and monitor all technical and screening matters for year-round film programmes, annual film festival, and other ancillary film programmes including but not limited to:
arrangements for censorship and co-ordination with OFNAA;
manage and carry out film/video checking;
manage  video editing, conversion and coordination of trailers, slides and other screening related materials production;
manage and assist in all subtitling production and projection issue;
liaise with screening venues and production houses;
co-ordinate subtitle production and provide onsite support for subtitle projection at the screening venues where necessary;
co-ordinating and taking care of setup and operations of online streaming platform;
co-ordinating events and activities (including the 46th HKIFF Opening, other Premiere events, online events and other Society organized events and activities);
monitor the projection and provide onsite support at screening venues;
assuming duties at HKIFF Temporary Office/ counter during the 46th HKIFF; and
Perform any other tasks as assigned by the immediate supervisor and/or management from time to time

Requirements:


University graduate or equivalent;
Good communication skills;
1 - 3 years’ working experience;
Excellent command of both written and spoken English and Chinese including Putonghua;
Proficient in foreign languages (Japanese, Korean, German, French, Italian, Spanish etc) will be an advance;
Proficient in Adobe Premiere Pro / Final Cut Pro / easyDCP Player/ subtitle editing software / Adobe Illustrator;
Proficient in PC skills (MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Access);
Knowledge of film format and video / film checking will be an advantage;
Knowledge of film subtitle production will be an advantage; Experience in technical coordination and working in film festival/film industry/production houses will be an advantage; and
Require to work overtime and at irregular hours including full-day work on weekends and public holidays during certain peak periods.
Candidates with less experience will be considered as Operations Assistant.


The above position is offered on temporary contract terms only.

Interested parties should apply with detailed resume stating current and expected salary to The HR & Administration Office, The Hong Kong International Film Festival Society at 8/F, The Rays, 71 Hung To Road, Kwun Tong or click "apply now" for application

(All personal data provided by applicants will be used for recruitment purpose only. Only those who are shortlisted will be contacted.)

Job Highlights

Plan and Execute the marketing campaigns and event production

Work with a project team to achieve client's goals

Flexible and friendly working style

Job Description

 What You Will Be Doing:

Manage digital campaign/ event production projects for clients

Work closely with vendors / internal teams to plan, develop, execute and implement digital marketing campaign/ event production projects;

Manage and analyze clients' digital performance from different industries

Study and document client’s requirements and provide suggestions / solutions based on client’s inquiries;

Communicate and solve problem during project period with clients;

Lead the kick-off meeting internally / with client.

Write up reports for clients about monthly updates, campaign effectiveness, marketing outcomes, data insights, competitor analysis, etc.

What You Need for this Position:

Degree or above;

1 years solid experience in project management/accounts servicing, preferably in managing online advertising and social media projects;

Fluent in written Chinese and English and spoken Mandarin, English and Cantonese;

Excellent communication, interpersonal and negotiation skills is a must;

Mature, attention to details and ability to work under tight timeline and multi-task independently;

Agency experiences are preferred;

Proficiency in MS office application;

Passionate and familiar with Social Media, with strong sense on social media trend 

Candidates with less experience will be also considered as Project Executive

Benefits We Offer:

5 days’ work
Medical Coverage
Snack Corner 
Birthday leaves
Fun, young and joyful environment

Responsibilities


Responsible to produce videos, include corporate videos, project videos, online marketing and other promotional materials, from pre-production, production to post-production;
Research and develop multimedia content to facilitate internal and external communications and support business needs;
Duties include strategic planning, shooting script work, casting, shot selection and editing, voiceover, audio input, subtitling, motion graphics, etc.;
Set up and execute occasional live-streaming broadcast.

Requirements

At least 2 years relevant working experience in multimedia production;
Proficient in video production and photo editing & retouching;
Familiar with Premiere Pro, Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects, etc.;
Able to work independently and under pressure;
Self-motivated, well organized and a good team player.

We offer competitive remuneration package with comprehensive fringe benefits to the right candidates:

- Birthday Leave / Marriage Leave / Paternity Leave / Examination Leave
- Staff Care Programme
- Career Development Programme


