Job Highlights
• Manage video and multimedia production projects
• Handle overall creative and production process
• Minimum 3 years’ relevant work experience

Job Description:
• Manage production of different video and multimedia projects, including handling from pre-production preparation, video shooting to post-production;
• Create and manage production budget;
• Manage overall production schedule and milestones;
• Contact different external partners/vendors for creative and production;
• Support Director and video crew onsite during video filming;
• Work with Director and Head of Production to make sure project on track and within budget;
• Collaborate with different teams, both in-house and 3rd party, to ensure the quality is met;

Requirements:
• Higher Diploma or above in TV, film, video production or related disciplines;
• Minimum 3 years’ relevant work experience; less experience will be considered as Associate Video Producer
• Understanding of video and various multimedia design workflows;
• Solid Project management Experience in this industry
• Willing to work on irregular hours;
• Knowledge in video, 2D /3D Animation, Design, photo / video shooting and field work;
• Ability to multitask and manage simultaneous projects;
• Proficient in Adobe Premiere and good knowledge in After Effects, Photoshop and Illustrator;
• Resourceful in video production vendors and partners
